WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.359
In our last study, we were in Genesis chapter number one,

00:00:03.359 --> 00:00:05.659
and we learned about God's name Elohim.

00:00:05.659 --> 00:00:06.820
That was two weeks ago.

00:00:06.820 --> 00:00:08.380
Last week, we had the weather

00:00:08.380 --> 00:00:10.939
and the uncertainty with ice and all of that,

00:00:10.939 --> 00:00:12.539
and so we did not have service,

00:00:12.539 --> 00:00:15.699
but we said this, that Elohim means strong one.

00:00:15.699 --> 00:00:19.700
It's used 32 times in Genesis chapter number one,

00:00:19.700 --> 00:00:22.180
and there's 31 verses in that chapter,

00:00:22.180 --> 00:00:26.940
and 32 times we read the word God, the English word,

00:00:26.940 --> 00:00:29.139
and it's Elohim, the Hebrew word,

00:00:29.139 --> 00:00:32.619
and we find that there's an obvious connection

00:00:32.619 --> 00:00:34.860
with the name of God Elohim

00:00:34.860 --> 00:00:37.540
to the fact that he is creator.

00:00:37.540 --> 00:00:41.099
This evening, as we come to Genesis chapter number 14,

00:00:41.099 --> 00:00:44.139
we're gonna learn about God's name El Elyon,

00:00:44.139 --> 00:00:46.659
and it's an interesting passage of scripture

00:00:46.659 --> 00:00:49.740
in which we'll kind of make our way through here quickly

00:00:49.740 --> 00:00:52.419
as we focus specifically on the name of God

00:00:52.419 --> 00:00:54.139
that is revealed to us here.

00:00:54.139 --> 00:00:57.860
El Elyon means the most high God,

00:00:57.860 --> 00:01:01.860
and I said to you last week that Elohim is the plural,

00:01:01.860 --> 00:01:03.380
El is the singular,

00:01:03.380 --> 00:01:07.819
and that oftentimes with the compound names of God,

00:01:07.819 --> 00:01:09.580
you'll see El,

00:01:09.580 --> 00:01:14.019
and then the other Hebrew word here this evening, El Elyon,

00:01:14.019 --> 00:01:16.019
and we'll see El Shaddai.

00:01:16.019 --> 00:01:17.419
There's a number of them,

00:01:17.419 --> 00:01:19.580
and El Shaddai is a very common one

00:01:19.580 --> 00:01:21.819
that many people are familiar with today,

00:01:21.819 --> 00:01:24.779
and so this evening in Genesis chapter number 14,

00:01:24.779 --> 00:01:28.500
there's a battle that takes place to begin the chapter.

00:01:28.500 --> 00:01:31.059
We're not gonna focus on that battle that takes place,

00:01:31.059 --> 00:01:33.940
but there's a number of things that take place there

00:01:33.940 --> 00:01:35.819
in the beginning verses of the scripture

00:01:35.819 --> 00:01:39.099
with regard to rebellion and fighting and battle

00:01:39.099 --> 00:01:40.379
and so on and so forth,

00:01:40.379 --> 00:01:42.300
and we find that one of the significant things

00:01:42.300 --> 00:01:45.540
that takes place is that Lot is taken captive,

00:01:45.540 --> 00:01:47.500
and when Lot is taken captive,

00:01:47.500 --> 00:01:49.260
the Bible tells us that Abram,

00:01:49.260 --> 00:01:50.620
his name's not been changed yet.

00:01:50.620 --> 00:01:53.980
I'll often refer to him as Abraham this evening,

00:01:53.980 --> 00:01:56.580
but Abraham did not go.

00:01:56.580 --> 00:01:57.900
Of course, he wasn't part of the battle,

00:01:57.900 --> 00:01:59.019
but he heard about,

00:01:59.019 --> 00:02:01.220
so then he does become part of the battle,

00:02:01.220 --> 00:02:05.099
and we read of that beginning in verse number 14,

00:02:05.099 --> 00:02:07.900
and we find that Abraham gets involved,

00:02:07.900 --> 00:02:11.380
and he has, he experiences complete victory.

00:02:11.380 --> 00:02:13.419
Notice in verse 14,

00:02:13.419 --> 00:02:14.259
the Bible says,

00:02:14.259 --> 00:02:17.779
and when Abram heard that his brother was taken captive,

00:02:17.779 --> 00:02:20.619
he armed his trained servants,

00:02:20.619 --> 00:02:23.740
born in his own house, 318,

00:02:23.740 --> 00:02:26.380
and pursued them unto Dan.

00:02:26.380 --> 00:02:29.619
Now, that's way up in the north part of Israel,

00:02:29.619 --> 00:02:31.059
and it's way up there in the north,

00:02:31.059 --> 00:02:32.539
and Dan, as you know,

00:02:32.539 --> 00:02:35.100
as we'll go through as you study through the scriptures

00:02:35.100 --> 00:02:37.860
and you find about what takes place there

00:02:37.860 --> 00:02:39.940
in the idol worship and all of that,

00:02:39.940 --> 00:02:41.259
but we find he is way up north,

00:02:41.259 --> 00:02:43.580
and it says that he divided himself against them,

00:02:43.580 --> 00:02:45.779
he and his servants, by night,

00:02:45.779 --> 00:02:49.059
and smote them and pursued them unto Hobah,

00:02:49.059 --> 00:02:51.779
which is on the left hand of Damascus,

00:02:51.779 --> 00:02:53.139
and then notice verse 16,

00:02:53.139 --> 00:02:55.380
this is where he experiences this complete victory,

00:02:55.380 --> 00:02:57.820
it says, and he brought back all the goods,

00:02:57.820 --> 00:03:01.139
and also brought again his brother Lot and his goods,

00:03:01.139 --> 00:03:04.500
and the women also, and the people.

00:03:04.500 --> 00:03:09.500
Immediately, as Abraham returns from this complete victory,

00:03:09.539 --> 00:03:11.059
he only gets involved

00:03:11.059 --> 00:03:14.100
because of finding out that Lot had been taken,

00:03:14.100 --> 00:03:16.820
and we find that he experiences this complete victory,

00:03:16.820 --> 00:03:18.300
and upon his return,

00:03:18.300 --> 00:03:20.580
we find that there are two interactions

00:03:20.580 --> 00:03:23.500
that are recorded for us in this text of scripture.

00:03:23.500 --> 00:03:26.740
One of them is with the king of Sodom,

00:03:26.740 --> 00:03:29.820
and the other one is with the king of Salem,

00:03:29.820 --> 00:03:32.059
and we find that the king of Sodom

00:03:32.059 --> 00:03:34.300
is mentioned here in verse number 17,

00:03:34.300 --> 00:03:37.940
and the first one that he would meet after this slaughter,

00:03:37.940 --> 00:03:41.860
and then the Bible immediately tells us in verse number 18

00:03:41.860 --> 00:03:43.779
that Melchizedek, king of Salem,

00:03:43.779 --> 00:03:45.419
brought forth bread and wine,

00:03:45.419 --> 00:03:48.059
and he was the priest of the most high God,

00:03:48.619 --> 00:03:50.699
and so this is the interaction that takes place.

00:03:50.699 --> 00:03:53.259
It's very interesting if you think about the timing

00:03:53.259 --> 00:03:54.539
of what goes on here,

00:03:54.539 --> 00:03:58.460
because Melchizedek speaks with Abraham,

00:03:58.460 --> 00:04:01.740
and God's name, El Elyon, is revealed to us

00:04:01.740 --> 00:04:04.539
for the first time in this text of scripture,

00:04:04.539 --> 00:04:06.259
and we find that it's of interest

00:04:06.259 --> 00:04:09.380
because in verse 17, it's the king of Sodom

00:04:09.380 --> 00:04:13.619
that first is going to meet Abram upon his return.

00:04:13.619 --> 00:04:17.179
Now, the king of Sodom is not able to give

00:04:17.179 --> 00:04:21.779
to Abram what his intended communication is

00:04:21.779 --> 00:04:23.779
until verse number 21,

00:04:23.779 --> 00:04:27.299
and in between verse 17 and verse 21

00:04:27.299 --> 00:04:30.059
is when Melchizedek, the king of Salem,

00:04:30.059 --> 00:04:34.100
comes in and has this conversation with Abram,

00:04:34.100 --> 00:04:35.859
and why is that so significant?

00:04:35.859 --> 00:04:39.540
Well, the reality is that what Abram,

00:04:39.540 --> 00:04:41.940
the truth that was revealed to Abraham

00:04:41.940 --> 00:04:44.700
from Melchizedek, the king of Salem,

00:04:44.700 --> 00:04:48.859
is a truth that is immediately given to us

00:04:48.859 --> 00:04:52.220
as having an immediate impact in his life,

00:04:52.220 --> 00:04:54.940
and so important that we understand that,

00:04:54.940 --> 00:04:58.660
again, when we speak about the various names of God,

00:04:58.660 --> 00:05:01.220
we've said this multiple times in this brief study.

00:05:01.220 --> 00:05:03.220
We've only been a few weeks in now,

00:05:03.220 --> 00:05:06.540
but we've said often that it's through the names

00:05:06.540 --> 00:05:09.619
that God is revealing to us various aspects

00:05:09.619 --> 00:05:12.019
of his nature and of his character,

00:05:12.019 --> 00:05:15.619
and so we find here that Melchizedek, in verse 18,

00:05:15.619 --> 00:05:17.339
we can notice, if you wanna take notes,

00:05:17.339 --> 00:05:21.779
notice number one, what Melchizedek says to Abraham

00:05:21.779 --> 00:05:25.059
and what he says about El Elyon, the Most High God,

00:05:25.059 --> 00:05:26.739
and we find that in verse 18 it says,

00:05:26.739 --> 00:05:28.299
"'In Melchizedek, king of Salem,

00:05:28.299 --> 00:05:30.459
"'brought forth bread and wine,

00:05:30.459 --> 00:05:34.380
"'and he was the priest of the Most High God.'"

00:05:34.380 --> 00:05:36.700
And so that's the Most High God there,

00:05:36.700 --> 00:05:38.779
that's El Elyon in the Hebrew,

00:05:38.779 --> 00:05:40.220
and in verse 19 it says,

00:05:40.220 --> 00:05:42.260
"'And he,' speaking of Melchizedek,

00:05:42.260 --> 00:05:44.140
"'blessed him,' speaking of Abraham,

00:05:44.140 --> 00:05:49.140
"'and said, Blessed be Abraham of the Most High God,

00:05:49.500 --> 00:05:53.459
"'possessor of heaven and earth.'"

00:05:53.459 --> 00:05:55.459
And so we find that as Melchizedek

00:05:55.459 --> 00:05:57.420
begins to have this conversation

00:05:57.420 --> 00:06:00.380
and this interaction is recorded for us,

00:06:00.380 --> 00:06:03.980
that he says to Abraham that he says,

00:06:04.019 --> 00:06:08.899
"'Blessed be Abraham of the Most High God.'"

00:06:08.899 --> 00:06:12.980
And this is the first time that this name is used,

00:06:12.980 --> 00:06:17.380
speaking of our God, and Abraham is being exposed

00:06:17.380 --> 00:06:20.820
after this battle, all that had taken place,

00:06:20.820 --> 00:06:22.660
Lot had been taken captive,

00:06:22.660 --> 00:06:25.339
all of these things going on, he comes back,

00:06:25.339 --> 00:06:26.739
the king of Sodom, of course,

00:06:26.739 --> 00:06:29.980
we know things about Sodom and Gomorrah and all of that,

00:06:29.980 --> 00:06:31.339
and all that would take place,

00:06:31.339 --> 00:06:33.779
and the king of Sodom is going to meet him,

00:06:34.579 --> 00:06:36.540
but before they can have a conversation,

00:06:36.540 --> 00:06:41.420
God ordains for Melchizedek to have this conversation.

00:06:41.420 --> 00:06:46.420
Now, if you study Psalm 101 and you look in Hebrews 7,

00:06:47.339 --> 00:06:50.820
you'll see further revelation for us

00:06:50.820 --> 00:06:53.260
with regard to Melchizedek,

00:06:53.260 --> 00:06:56.820
and the Lord Jesus Christ is not a priest

00:06:56.820 --> 00:07:01.260
after the order of Aaron, the Aaronic priesthood,

00:07:01.260 --> 00:07:03.820
but after the order of Melchizedek,

00:07:03.820 --> 00:07:05.380
and you'll see that connection,

00:07:05.380 --> 00:07:08.420
but we really wanna focus on the message

00:07:08.420 --> 00:07:10.100
that is delivered to Abraham,

00:07:10.100 --> 00:07:14.220
because here, what's happening is God is allowing

00:07:14.220 --> 00:07:16.619
for Abraham to understand something

00:07:16.619 --> 00:07:19.540
about the character and nature of God

00:07:19.540 --> 00:07:23.739
that before this moment, he didn't fully understand.

00:07:23.739 --> 00:07:26.179
And so what is it that he's going to reveal to him?

00:07:26.179 --> 00:07:28.380
Well, that he is the Most High God, first of all,

00:07:28.380 --> 00:07:30.820
but then he says this at the end of verse number 19,

00:07:30.859 --> 00:07:35.779
that he is the possessor of heaven and earth.

00:07:35.779 --> 00:07:38.500
It's interesting because when we looked at the name Elohim,

00:07:38.500 --> 00:07:41.059
we find that God reveals to us

00:07:41.059 --> 00:07:43.859
that yes, he is the strong one,

00:07:43.859 --> 00:07:46.500
but there's that connection with the name Elohim

00:07:46.500 --> 00:07:49.140
with creation, that he is the creator.

00:07:49.140 --> 00:07:52.000
Not only is he creator, Elohim,

00:07:52.000 --> 00:07:56.540
but he is the possessor of heaven and earth, El Elyon,

00:07:56.540 --> 00:07:59.299
the Most High God, who is also the possessor.

00:07:59.299 --> 00:08:01.859
He created and it's his.

00:08:01.859 --> 00:08:03.279
I want you to think about that this evening,

00:08:03.279 --> 00:08:05.739
just for a moment, when we think about our own lives,

00:08:05.739 --> 00:08:08.420
that he created man, that we're created in his image,

00:08:08.420 --> 00:08:10.739
and of course, we understand through the fall

00:08:10.739 --> 00:08:11.660
and all of those things,

00:08:11.660 --> 00:08:14.700
but as we've been reconciled, redeemed this evening,

00:08:14.700 --> 00:08:18.380
for those of us that are saved, that we belong to God.

00:08:18.380 --> 00:08:21.940
He is our Lord and our master,

00:08:21.940 --> 00:08:23.279
and we'll look at that next week

00:08:23.279 --> 00:08:26.459
as we enter into chapter number 15

00:08:26.459 --> 00:08:29.459
and looking at the name Adonai, Lord,

00:08:29.459 --> 00:08:32.539
and we find here that he is,

00:08:32.539 --> 00:08:35.780
Abraham is receiving this information

00:08:35.780 --> 00:08:38.500
that God is the Most High God

00:08:38.500 --> 00:08:40.460
and he is the possessor of heaven and earth.

00:08:40.460 --> 00:08:42.700
Notice, if you will, just a couple of verses of scripture.

00:08:42.700 --> 00:08:45.260
Hold your place there in Genesis chapter 14,

00:08:45.260 --> 00:08:47.940
but look over in the book of Exodus in chapter nine,

00:08:47.940 --> 00:08:50.080
and I want you to notice what Moses

00:08:50.080 --> 00:08:52.099
is going to say to Pharaoh,

00:08:52.099 --> 00:08:55.099
and of course, we know some things about Egypt

00:08:55.140 --> 00:08:58.859
and about their polytheism and all that was going on there,

00:08:58.859 --> 00:09:02.659
and we find that Moses is going to have this conversation

00:09:02.659 --> 00:09:04.760
in the midst of the plagues.

00:09:04.760 --> 00:09:08.039
In Exodus nine, where we're gonna look at in verse 29,

00:09:08.039 --> 00:09:09.979
is during the seventh plague,

00:09:09.979 --> 00:09:11.940
and we find that Moses says this.

00:09:11.940 --> 00:09:14.580
Notice in Exodus nine in verse 29,

00:09:14.580 --> 00:09:16.380
and Moses said unto him,

00:09:16.380 --> 00:09:18.219
as soon as I am gone out of the city,

00:09:18.219 --> 00:09:20.700
I will spread abroad my hands unto the Lord.

00:09:20.700 --> 00:09:23.179
Now, that's all caps, that's Jehovah,

00:09:23.179 --> 00:09:26.500
and it says this, and the thunder shall cease,

00:09:26.500 --> 00:09:29.140
neither shall there be any more hail.

00:09:29.140 --> 00:09:31.500
Notice that thou mayest know

00:09:31.500 --> 00:09:35.760
how that the earth is the Lord's,

00:09:35.760 --> 00:09:40.760
and we talk about this phrase back in Genesis chapter 14,

00:09:40.840 --> 00:09:45.640
that the Most High God, the possessor of heaven and earth,

00:09:45.640 --> 00:09:48.219
and here, we find that it's of interest

00:09:48.219 --> 00:09:50.400
in Exodus chapter number nine

00:09:50.440 --> 00:09:54.159
that Moses is going to speak to Pharaoh.

00:09:54.159 --> 00:09:56.320
Of course, we know by this time

00:09:56.320 --> 00:10:00.159
that many of the magicians in these.

00:10:00.159 --> 00:10:01.759
religious people there.

00:10:01.759 --> 00:10:03.879
They've already said to Pharaoh,

00:10:03.879 --> 00:10:05.279
this is the finger of God.

00:10:05.279 --> 00:10:06.559
Don't you know what's happened?

00:10:06.559 --> 00:10:09.739
How long are you gonna let them do these things?

00:10:09.739 --> 00:10:11.619
I mean, the land is desolate.

00:10:11.619 --> 00:10:14.239
And here we find that Moses says,

00:10:14.239 --> 00:10:17.879
I'm gonna go out and I'm gonna spread my hands to the Lord

00:10:17.879 --> 00:10:19.739
and all of it's gonna cease.

00:10:20.719 --> 00:10:21.959
But it's not because of me.

00:10:21.959 --> 00:10:23.439
It's not because of my power.

00:10:23.439 --> 00:10:28.159
It's because God is revealing to you who he is

00:10:28.279 --> 00:10:33.279
and that you would know that the earth is the Lord's.

00:10:34.279 --> 00:10:37.259
And we live in a time today that there are many people

00:10:37.259 --> 00:10:39.639
that have misunderstanding with regard to,

00:10:39.639 --> 00:10:41.379
you'll hear people talk about mother nature.

00:10:41.379 --> 00:10:43.159
You'll hear people talk about all these things

00:10:43.159 --> 00:10:45.679
with climate, this and that, so on and so forth.

00:10:45.679 --> 00:10:49.639
And the reality is that God is not only the creator,

00:10:49.639 --> 00:10:53.919
but he's the possessor and he is the sustainer.

00:10:53.919 --> 00:10:56.079
And we see that throughout the scriptures.

00:10:56.079 --> 00:10:58.279
In the book of Deuteronomy in chapter 32,

00:10:58.279 --> 00:11:00.639
notice what the Bible says here

00:11:00.639 --> 00:11:04.219
with regard to this same truth and same idea

00:11:04.219 --> 00:11:08.199
with regard to El Elyon, the most high God.

00:11:08.199 --> 00:11:11.119
In Deuteronomy chapter 32, it's the song of Moses.

00:11:11.119 --> 00:11:13.959
We're near the end of the book of Deuteronomy

00:11:13.959 --> 00:11:16.959
and we understand that Moses will soon die

00:11:16.959 --> 00:11:19.399
and then Joshua will be the human leader

00:11:19.399 --> 00:11:22.439
to take the children of Israel into the land of promise.

00:11:22.439 --> 00:11:25.239
And we find that as you look at the song of Moses

00:11:25.239 --> 00:11:28.519
here in Deuteronomy 32, notice in verse number eight,

00:11:28.519 --> 00:11:31.679
the Bible says this, when the most high,

00:11:31.679 --> 00:11:33.879
that's El Elyon, that's the Hebrew there,

00:11:33.879 --> 00:11:38.199
when the most high divided to the nations

00:11:38.199 --> 00:11:43.199
their inheritance, when he separated the sons of Adam,

00:11:43.399 --> 00:11:45.399
he set the bounds of the people

00:11:45.399 --> 00:11:48.799
according to the number of the children of Israel.

00:11:48.799 --> 00:11:53.119
Now why is that significant that Moses would reference this

00:11:53.119 --> 00:11:55.039
and why he would use this terminology?

00:11:55.759 --> 00:11:56.599
Well, of course we know all scripture

00:11:56.599 --> 00:11:57.839
is given by inspiration of God,

00:11:57.839 --> 00:12:02.279
but it's certainly interesting that when this name of God

00:12:02.279 --> 00:12:05.999
is first revealed to us in Genesis chapter 14,

00:12:05.999 --> 00:12:09.159
the Bible tells us that he is the possessor

00:12:09.159 --> 00:12:10.639
of heaven and earth.

00:12:10.639 --> 00:12:13.519
And if he is the possessor of heaven and earth,

00:12:13.519 --> 00:12:18.519
then it's well within his right, and I know he's God

00:12:19.359 --> 00:12:21.479
and so don't misunderstand how I'm saying that,

00:12:21.479 --> 00:12:24.479
but he is the one that's going to give the land

00:12:24.519 --> 00:12:27.159
to whom he's going to give the land to.

00:12:27.159 --> 00:12:27.999
Why?

00:12:27.999 --> 00:12:29.719
Because he's the possessor of heaven and earth,

00:12:29.719 --> 00:12:33.319
he's the creator, it's his, and here we find that Moses,

00:12:33.319 --> 00:12:36.599
while he's rejoicing, he speaks about the most high,

00:12:36.599 --> 00:12:39.559
how he divided to the nations their inheritance

00:12:39.559 --> 00:12:41.599
when he separated the sons of Adam

00:12:41.599 --> 00:12:43.879
and God is the one that's in control.

00:12:43.879 --> 00:12:48.759
Paul mentions in 1 Corinthians chapter 10 in verse number 26

00:12:48.759 --> 00:12:52.559
to keep the thought even to the New Testament

00:12:52.559 --> 00:12:56.359
in understanding this truth with regard to the Lord

00:12:56.359 --> 00:12:59.359
being the possessor of heaven and earth,

00:12:59.359 --> 00:13:01.599
the Bible says in 1 Corinthians 10 in verse 26,

00:13:01.599 --> 00:13:06.399
for the earth is the Lord's and the fullness thereof.

00:13:06.399 --> 00:13:08.239
The earth is the Lord's.

00:13:08.239 --> 00:13:11.239
Now he gave us a responsibility to be stewards

00:13:11.239 --> 00:13:14.399
