of who God is, but for those of us that know him,

00:27:38.000 --> 00:27:40.359
we ought to desire to make him known.

00:27:42.160 --> 00:27:45.279
I was having a conversation yesterday,

00:27:45.279 --> 00:27:48.920
really just challenging myself

00:27:48.920 --> 00:27:52.480
and thinking about this truth

00:27:52.480 --> 00:27:55.959
of how much do we wanna make our God known?

00:27:55.959 --> 00:27:57.880
And we know how great he is,

00:27:57.880 --> 00:28:00.839
but we also recognize that so many

00:28:00.839 --> 00:28:03.480
are ignorant of his greatness.

00:28:04.079 --> 00:28:05.880
They don't know that he is the redeemer.

00:28:05.880 --> 00:28:08.320
They don't know, as we're looking this evening,

00:28:08.320 --> 00:28:10.480
that he is the most high God.

00:28:10.480 --> 00:28:13.519
And I asked myself this question of,

00:28:13.519 --> 00:28:16.859
when's the last time I've shared the gospel with someone?

00:28:17.799 --> 00:28:19.119
And I was able to answer the question,

00:28:19.119 --> 00:28:20.640
I was able to go back in my mind

00:28:20.640 --> 00:28:23.799
and I could see the place, I could take you there right now

00:28:23.799 --> 00:28:26.200
and I could see the face of the individual

00:28:26.200 --> 00:28:29.799
that I most recently shared the gospel with one-on-one.

00:28:30.799 --> 00:28:33.020
I wish they trust that Christ is their savior,

00:28:33.859 --> 00:28:35.979
but they didn't, I have no control over that

00:28:35.979 --> 00:28:37.739
and neither do you.

00:28:37.739 --> 00:28:40.419
But what we must really ask ourselves this evening

00:28:40.419 --> 00:28:43.460
is when's the last time I've told anybody about my God?

00:28:44.419 --> 00:28:48.020
I'm talking about somebody that's not already in the church,

00:28:48.020 --> 00:28:51.020
somebody that doesn't already know how good our God is.

00:28:51.020 --> 00:28:53.700
It's easy for us to talk one to another and say,

00:28:53.700 --> 00:28:55.059
man, isn't God so good?

00:28:55.059 --> 00:28:57.619
And he answered prayer and he did this and that's wonderful.

00:28:57.619 --> 00:29:00.280
And it strengthens us and it sharpens us,

00:29:00.280 --> 00:29:03.400
but the reality is that the prayer of the psalmist here

00:29:03.400 --> 00:29:05.599
is that others would know.

00:29:06.719 --> 00:29:09.159
We ought to have that same desire.

00:29:09.159 --> 00:29:14.159
I'm thankful this evening that God has revealed truth to us,

00:29:14.239 --> 00:29:18.760
but often said and known by all of us here this evening

00:29:18.760 --> 00:29:21.780
to whom much is given, much is required.

00:29:21.780 --> 00:29:24.719
Psalm 91 and we'll finish here.

00:29:24.719 --> 00:29:27.859
This is the Psalm that we started with a few weeks ago

00:29:27.859 --> 00:29:32.859
and verse 14 is being kind of our starting point

00:29:32.859 --> 00:29:34.780
for this whole study on the names of God.

00:29:34.780 --> 00:29:38.419
But we see in Psalm 91 in verse number one,

00:29:38.419 --> 00:29:43.419
he that dwelleth in the secret place of the Most High

00:29:43.580 --> 00:29:48.059
shall abide under the shadow of the Almighty.

00:29:48.059 --> 00:29:51.760
I will say of the Lord, he is my refuge and my fortress,

00:29:51.760 --> 00:29:56.219
my God in him will I trust.

00:29:56.219 --> 00:29:58.380
I mentioned to you when we looked at this Psalm

00:29:58.380 --> 00:29:59.219
a few weeks ago.

00:29:59.219 --> 00:30:04.419
that there are several names of God that are used in those first two verses.

00:30:04.419 --> 00:30:06.619
But I want to focus this evening when the Bible says,

00:30:06.619 --> 00:30:11.119
He that dwelleth in the secret place of the Most High

00:30:11.119 --> 00:30:15.419
shall abide under the shadow of the Almighty.

00:30:15.419 --> 00:30:19.319
We should think about those two words, dwelleth and abide.

00:30:19.319 --> 00:30:23.219
You know, it's a wonderful thing that the Most High God,

00:30:23.219 --> 00:30:26.519
the possessor of heaven and earth,

00:30:26.519 --> 00:30:33.019
that He would allow us to dwell and abide in His presence.

00:30:33.019 --> 00:30:34.619
Isn't that amazing?

00:30:34.619 --> 00:30:40.219
I know it's Wednesday evening, I know we know the Lord,

00:30:40.219 --> 00:30:43.419
but I hope tonight we can just take a step back

00:30:43.419 --> 00:30:49.219
and just stand once again amazed at the very truth

00:30:49.219 --> 00:30:54.319
that the Most High God, the possessor of heaven and earth,

00:30:54.319 --> 00:30:59.919
He allows for us, and you know you better than anyone else knows you.

00:30:59.919 --> 00:31:04.819
You know your weaknesses and you know your strengths.

00:31:04.819 --> 00:31:06.719
You know everything about you.

00:31:06.719 --> 00:31:11.019
You know things about yourself that no one else knows about you.

00:31:11.019 --> 00:31:16.519
And then God knows everything with perfect wisdom.

00:31:16.519 --> 00:31:18.819
And the Most High God, possessor of heaven and earth,

00:31:18.819 --> 00:31:24.819
He allows us to dwell and to abide in His presence.

00:31:24.819 --> 00:31:26.819
It's amazing to me.

00:31:26.819 --> 00:31:30.219
It's amazing to me that God would love us so much

00:31:30.219 --> 00:31:34.019
that He wants to reveal Himself to us.

00:31:34.019 --> 00:31:39.619
And He uses these names to help us understand

00:31:39.619 --> 00:31:42.819
with a deeper level of clarity,

00:31:42.819 --> 00:31:46.719
His nature and His character and His attributes.

00:31:46.719 --> 00:31:49.319
And He wants us to know tonight that He's the Most High God.

00:31:49.319 --> 00:31:51.519
He's the possessor of heaven and earth.

00:31:51.519 --> 00:31:57.219
And I'm thankful this evening for the truth of Genesis chapter 14

00:31:57.219 --> 00:32:01.619
and the timing of the whole thing and how God allowed for,

00:32:01.619 --> 00:32:03.819
yes, the King of Sodom was coming,

00:32:03.819 --> 00:32:09.419
but oh, the King of Salem got there and was able to reveal truth to Abraham

00:32:09.419 --> 00:32:14.819
that He needed in that very moment of what He was going to deal with.

00:32:14.919 --> 00:32:18.319
And this evening, we deal with things all the time.

00:32:18.319 --> 00:32:21.319
And we need to know that our God is the Most High God.

00:32:21.319 --> 00:32:24.119
He is the possessor of heaven and earth.

00:32:24.119 --> 00:32:27.519
Let's pray, Father, how we love You tonight.

00:32:27.519 --> 00:32:32.719
And I pray that You would help us, Lord, to recognize You for who You are.

00:32:32.719 --> 00:32:38.819
I pray, God, that You would help us tonight to abide and dwell in Your presence.

00:32:38.819 --> 00:32:45.119
What a privilege. What a privilege that we have.

00:32:45.119 --> 00:32:48.319
God, I pray that You'd give us a burden.

00:32:48.319 --> 00:32:54.319
As we read there the Psalm of Asaph, as we think about Paul in Athens,

00:32:54.319 --> 00:32:58.719
a burden that others might know who You are.

00:32:58.719 --> 00:33:04.719
We thank You for giving us this revealed truth,

00:33:04.719 --> 00:33:10.719
and we understand the responsibility that is ours to make You known.

00:33:10.719 --> 00:33:13.219
Would You help us to be faithful?

00:33:13.219 --> 00:33:18.219
Would You help us to be diligent to teach these truths to a generation

00:33:18.219 --> 00:33:23.719
that's coming behind us into a world that's lost and dying?

00:33:23.719 --> 00:33:25.219
Thank You for the privilege of prayer.

00:33:25.219 --> 00:33:28.219
We pray that You'd be honored and glorified through all that's said and done.

00:33:28.219 --> 00:33:31.719
For it's in Christ's name we pray. Amen.

00:33:31.719 --> 00:33:34.219
Does anyone need a prayer bulletin this evening? You got one?

00:33:34.219 --> 00:33:34.719
No?

